<!-- ═══ FINDINGS ═══ -->
<div class="section-label">Section 07 &mdash; Key Findings</div>
<h2 class="section-title">What the Data Tells Us</h2>

<div class="findings-grid">
  <div>
    <div class="finding-num">FINDING 01</div>
    <div class="finding-title">Reputation without visibility is invisible revenue loss</div>
    <div class="finding-body">Seven companies in this market have exceptional ratings — 4.9 to 5.0 stars, often with hundreds of verified reviews. Wyman Plumbing has 1,517 five-star reviews. Elite Rooter has 1,405. Yet they rank #13 and #14 in the Map Pack at best. A homeowner searching at 10pm does not know those reviews exist. The best plumber in Phoenix is not winning. The most visible one is.</div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="finding-num">FINDING 02</div>
    <div class="finding-title">Map Pack positions drive 60–70% of all clicks</div>
    <div class="finding-body">For local intent searches in Phoenix, the Google Maps 3-pack captures more traffic than organic and paid combined. Companies outside the top 3 are effectively invisible. This is why Maloney Plumbing holds #3 despite not ranking in organic, and why Benjamin Franklin's strong organic presence matters less than their mid-pack Maps position.</div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="finding-num">FINDING 03</div>
    <div class="finding-title">Review volume is now a ranking factor that compounds</div>
    <div class="finding-body">Parker &amp; Sons' 32,563 reviews is not just social proof — it is a structural ranking advantage that increases monthly. They accumulate reviews faster because they get more visibility, which drives more jobs, which generates more reviews. The top position becomes more entrenched over time, not less.</div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="finding-num">FINDING 04</div>
    <div class="finding-title">The window for secondary terms is measurably open</div>
    <div class="finding-body">Water heater repair, drain cleaning, emergency plumbing, and sewer repair terms still have contested or open Map Pack positions. Operators with perfect 5.0 ratings are ranked #8, #9, #12, and #14. A focused 90-day effort on GBP optimization, review velocity, and service-area pages can move these positions. That window closes as competitive investment increases.</div>
  </div>
</div>

